  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge and open the packet to let it air</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> sweet potato[es] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1672853653394-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1672853653394-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1672853653394-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1672853653394-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1672853653394-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>red onion[s]</strong>, then chop the <strong>remaining red onion </strong>into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>to a bowl, cover with <strong>boiled water </strong>and set aside</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672853656147-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672853656147-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672853656147-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672853656147-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672853656147-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>and <strong>chopped sweet potato </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with the<strong> chopped pepper</strong>, <strong>onion wedges </strong>and 2/3<strong> </strong>of the <strong>grated garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add your <strong>ras el hanout </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> to the tray[s] with<strong> </strong>a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the chicken is golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) and the veg is tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672853659881-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672853659881-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672853659881-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672853659881-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672853659881-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, combine your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> with the <strong>remaining grated garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) in a bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– this your <strong>garlic yoghurt</strong></p>",
